1
00:00:03,090 --> 00:00:04,730
I bought some congee for you.

2
00:00:04,730 --> 00:00:06,120
I actually bought two for both of you.

3
00:00:06,120 --> 00:00:08,443
You remember I don't like livers.

4
00:00:08,443 --> 00:00:10,923
Well, the store told me they ran out of livers.

5
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:16,040
You kept saying you didn't want to do this job,

6
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:17,770
but you tried to get close to him!

7
00:00:17,770 --> 00:00:20,890
You went beyond your responsibility. That's why things have gone too far up to now!

8
00:00:20,890 --> 00:00:22,320
Take it and don't come to work again.

9
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:24,980
I really pity myself.

10
00:00:24,980 --> 00:00:28,315
Feel free to cry, Miss Pam. No one can see you now.

11
00:00:36,940 --> 00:00:39,750
- Well...
- Yes. I'm coming.

12
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:02,340
Mom.

13
00:01:02,340 --> 00:01:03,720
How is Dad?

14
00:01:03,720 --> 00:01:06,160
Did anyone give you an update on his condition yet?

15
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:07,250
Not yet.

16
00:01:07,250 --> 00:01:08,680
He has been in there since this afternoon.

17
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:10,490
It's nearly 8:00 p.m. now.

18
00:01:10,490 --> 00:01:13,008
He hasn't had the operation yet.

19
00:01:14,150 --> 00:01:15,720
Come on.

20
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:17,940
He will recover soon.

21
00:01:17,940 --> 00:01:20,319
He's bold.

22
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,730
Where is Pam?

23
00:01:26,730 --> 00:01:29,783
She went back home to grab some stuff. She'll be here soon.

24
00:01:34,890 --> 00:01:39,119
Why is Dad in this condition all of a sudden?

25
00:01:39,119 --> 00:01:42,241
He was just discharged from the hospital, wasn't he?

26
00:01:42,241 --> 00:01:46,296
Earlier today, when we were having lunch, he blacked out.

27
00:01:46,860 --> 00:01:49,000
I guess he's worried about Pam.

28
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,600
She's working, so she comes home late.

29
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,120
Your dad is so worried about her that he couldn't sleep.

30
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,880
But I won't blame Pam for this.

31
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:59,600
This is what being old is like. We get sick easily.

32
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:03,620
But Pam blames herself for what happened,

33
00:02:03,620 --> 00:02:06,224
so she's going to quit.

34
00:02:07,690 --> 00:02:09,249
Is that so?

35
00:02:10,890 --> 00:02:14,490
She told you she'd quit because of this?

36
00:02:16,670 --> 00:02:19,300
Did she talk to you about something else?

37
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:22,819
Nope. She only talked about Grandpa.

38
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:38,010
Miss Pam.

39
00:02:38,010 --> 00:02:39,410
Yes?

40
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,970
Where did you get it?

41
00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:55,170
He asked me to give it to you when you were in the house getting your stuff.

42
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:03,752
Why didn't you tell me he came, Mr. Aood?

43
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:10,535
If he wanted to see you, he wouldn't have left first.

44
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:14,060
I kind of understand why.

45
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:16,910
It's because we just fought earlier today.

46
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:26,274
Did he see me cry?

47
00:03:27,842 --> 00:03:29,861
I don't know either.

48
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:35,980
Are you afraid that he saw you cry

49
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:40,414
or that he saw you cry with me?

50
00:03:43,660 --> 00:03:46,213
I'm just asking.

51
00:03:48,690 --> 00:03:49,890
Right.

52
00:04:07,860 --> 00:04:09,083
Hello, Pete.

53
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:11,483
Did you talk to Pam?

54
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,074
Not yet.

55
00:04:13,074 --> 00:04:16,549
You said you'd say sorry to her, didn't you?

56
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:18,610
I haven't met her yet.

57
00:04:18,610 --> 00:04:20,600
She went back home to get her stuff.

58
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,440
When you talk to her, try to calm yourself down.

59
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:24,460
Don't explode your anger at her again.

60
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,231
I just talked to my mom.

61
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:31,660
She told me Pam is going to quit.

62
00:04:31,660 --> 00:04:33,420
That's not surprising though.

63
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:35,650
Pam is a kindergarten teacher.

64
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:37,330
She has her daily routine.

65
00:04:37,330 --> 00:04:40,740
Being Donovan's manager is a complete contrast with that, isn't it?

66
00:04:40,740 --> 00:04:42,810
She left in the morning and came back home another morning.

67
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:46,010
What's more, her own mom scolded her.

68
00:04:46,010 --> 00:04:48,260
When she argued back, you slapped her.

69
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:52,013
How could she bear it? No doubt she told Grandma about that.

70
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:57,489
If you called to add insult to injury, just hang up.

71
00:04:58,090 --> 00:05:00,524
I already feel bad now.

72
00:05:06,810 --> 00:05:08,410
Pete,

73
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:15,769
Pam didn't tell Grandma about me scolding or slapping her at all.

74
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:21,102
This makes me feel even more awful now.

75
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:27,000
What do you think I should do?

76
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,500
Say sorry to her.

77
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:32,000
You went there to say sorry to her, didn't you?

78
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,253
Just tell her you're foul-mouthed,

79
00:05:34,253 --> 00:05:36,950
and treated her so badly.

80
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,291
I'm back.

81
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,920
What did the doctor say?

82
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:06,638
He hasn't come out yet.

83
00:06:09,690 --> 00:06:11,490
Pam.

84
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:15,929
Let's talk.

85
00:06:17,030 --> 00:06:21,300
It's difficult to make eye contact with the person we're angry with.

86
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:23,980
I don't even want to look at her face.

87
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,923
Miss Pam can't see you now.

88
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:47,060
Please give her this.

89
00:06:47,060 --> 00:06:48,660
I'll bring it to her.

90
00:06:48,660 --> 00:06:50,560
Why did Pam cry?

91
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:53,170
Her grandpa has to undergo an emergency operation.

92
00:06:53,170 --> 00:06:54,690
Is Pam all right now?

93
00:06:54,690 --> 00:06:56,170
Miss Pam was doing okay before,

94
00:06:56,170 --> 00:06:59,620
but ever since you stepped into her life, she's facing all these problems.

95
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:01,920
This was the first time she cried.

96
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:05,240
I think you should find a new manager.

97
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,260
I want to see the old Miss Pam.

98
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:09,220
The one who used to be happy.

99
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:11,260
I don't want to see her cry anymore.

100
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:13,784
Especially for someone like you.

101
00:07:16,820 --> 00:07:18,820
Why do I suck at everything?

102
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:20,520
Why am I always wrong?

103
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,850
I'm a troublemaker.

104
00:07:21,850 --> 00:07:23,950
I shouldn't have been born.

105
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:25,770
Don't think like that.

106
00:07:25,770 --> 00:07:27,120
You're speaking nonsense right now.

107
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,500
Yes.

108
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:30,420
I'm full of nonsense. So what?

109
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:34,700
Scold me and let it end with me.

110
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:44,240
But ever since you stepped into her life, she's facing all these problems.

111
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:46,310
I shouldn't have been born.

112
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:47,770
I'm a troublemaker.

113
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:49,000
I'm a troublemaker.

114
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,980
- I shouldn't have been born.
- She's facing all these problems.

115
00:07:50,980 --> 00:07:53,120
This was the first time she cried.

116
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:57,080
"I want to see the old Miss Pam. The one who used to be happy."

117
00:07:57,080 --> 00:08:02,800
"I don't want to see her cry anymore. Especially for someone like you."

118
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:09,160
Because of Mr. Aood's words, Donovan is now drowning in guilt.

119
00:08:27,410 --> 00:08:28,978
Does it hurt?

120
00:08:37,530 --> 00:08:39,511
I'm sorry.

121
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:48,393
It's pretty surprising to me that the first thing a person like Mom says is sorry.

122
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:53,020
I thought it over.

123
00:08:53,020 --> 00:08:56,439
I spoke with and treated you too badly, Pam.

124
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:02,231
To be honest, we haven't lived together for 20 years.

125
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:06,753
Sometimes, I forget that you're my daughter.

126
00:09:07,430 --> 00:09:09,640
She forgets that I'm her daughter?

127
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:13,450
This following sentence from her surprises me as well.

128
00:09:13,450 --> 00:09:15,976
Anyway, I'm sorry.

129
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:19,321
I'll try to control my emotions.

130
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:22,251
Okay?

131
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:30,480
Actually, I'm all right.

132
00:09:32,610 --> 00:09:36,690
I also want to say sorry for causing you problems all the time.

133
00:09:36,690 --> 00:09:39,340
Just forget about it.

134
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:41,506
Let's start again.

135
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,960
Yes.

136
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:04,210
I'm returning this to you.

137
00:10:39,740 --> 00:10:44,640
Because of this incident, family members who haven't lived together for so many years

138
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:47,843
have to spend several hours together.

139
00:10:57,950 --> 00:10:58,810
Doctor.

140
00:10:58,810 --> 00:11:00,610
Doctor!

141
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:03,940
How is he now?

142
00:11:04,370 --> 00:11:10,696
Our wait is over now.

143
00:11:10,696 --> 00:11:15,600
Perhaps it's because someone heard Grandma and me praying.

144
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:18,767
We feel that it has been such an eternally long time.

145
00:11:18,767 --> 00:11:20,803
It has come to an end, finally.

146
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:35,401
Everything is all right now, Grandma.

147
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,880
What time is it, Pam?

148
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:44,800
When the thing I have focused on is over now,

149
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:49,868
it comes to my mind that someone might be waiting for me.

150
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,000
You're speaking nonsense right now.

151
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,330
Yes.

152
00:11:53,330 --> 00:11:55,460
Scold me.

153
00:11:55,460 --> 00:11:58,560
Should I contact him?

154
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:01,760
Perhaps, he must be sleeping already,

155
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:04,700
or he hasn't been waiting for me at all.

156
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,300
Miss Pam?

157
00:12:06,970 --> 00:12:08,770
Yes.

158
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:10,760
What did you say?

159
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:12,280
It's 3.30 a.m. now.

160
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:14,650
I already told your mom.

161
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:21,160
The hospital won't allow us to see him today.

162
00:12:21,160 --> 00:12:23,539
Let's go home for now.

163
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,680
All right.

164
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,203
I'll send you home.

165
00:12:27,203 --> 00:12:29,135
It's all right, Mom.

166
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:32,608
I drove here.

167
00:12:32,608 --> 00:12:33,920
Let's go.

168
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,698
Let's go, Mr. Aood.

169
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:41,527
You two are still not okay with each other?

170
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,680
- Huh?
- Your mom and you.

171
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:47,100
You guys haven't reconciled?

172
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:51,510
This is Grandma. She knows me best and reads my mind best.

173
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:56,370
Pam, I understand that this problem happened a long time ago,

174
00:12:56,370 --> 00:13:00,980
so you guys can't settle it down right away after just a few conversations.

175
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:02,730
But listen to me, Pam.

176
00:13:02,730 --> 00:13:05,000
Time can't be turned back,

177
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,960
and it never stops either.

178
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:11,570
She also likes to say things that hit me hard.

179
00:13:11,570 --> 00:13:13,070
Let's go.

180
00:13:14,970 --> 00:13:17,360
Grandpa is all right now.

181
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,241
Let's go back to rest.

182
00:13:40,217 --> 00:13:42,490
Sa, what's wrong? Are you hurt?

183
00:13:42,490 --> 00:13:45,921
You should have told me. I can do that for you.

184
00:13:45,921 --> 00:13:48,040
I'm fine. Just tight tendons.

185
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,370
It's not because I'm old though.

186
00:13:50,370 --> 00:13:52,671
It's because I didn't get enough rest. Got it?

187
00:13:52,671 --> 00:13:53,860
Yeah.

188
00:13:53,860 --> 00:13:56,140
I didn't say anything.

189
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:57,520
Go and get some rest now.

190
00:13:57,520 --> 00:14:00,160
Pam, you must get some rest too.

191
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:01,560
Don't stress yourself out.

192
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:03,290
Grandpa is safe now.

193
00:14:03,290 --> 00:14:05,680
Don't be stressed. Got it?

194
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:07,160
- Okay?
- Yes.

195
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:09,060
You too.

196
00:14:09,060 --> 00:14:10,570
Let's go.

197
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:14,850
Wait.

198
00:14:14,850 --> 00:14:16,820
Face me.

199
00:14:16,820 --> 00:14:18,410
You said you wouldn't stress yourself out, didn't you?

200
00:14:18,410 --> 00:14:20,330
But why are you frowning?

201
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:23,800
Botox can't even help you with that.

202
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:26,580
All right.

203
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:30,600
How is it?

204
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,000
Fab.

205
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:39,420
Sa, don't worry about me.

206
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,760
I can take care of myself.

207
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:42,970
You'd better take care of yourself.

208
00:14:42,970 --> 00:14:45,560
Look at you now.

209
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:48,230
Come on. We're not different.

210
00:14:48,230 --> 00:14:49,720
Go and take a shower now.

211
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:51,860
I'll turn on super cool air for you.

212
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:54,040
Okay. Go and get some rest.

213
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:56,329
Take care of yourself, too.

214
00:14:56,330 --> 00:14:57,740
I'm going.

215
00:14:57,740 --> 00:15:00,480
Watch your back too. Be careful when you bend down.

216
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:03,518
Happy now? It's straight already.

217
00:15:07,690 --> 00:15:09,924
Since last night,

218
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:14,301
he had disappeared, not contacting me again.

219
00:15:16,730 --> 00:15:20,793
I should clear things up with him now.

220
00:15:51,110 --> 00:15:53,150
[Pam]

221
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:11,420
Hello?

222
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,998
Are you still on the call?

223
00:16:17,770 --> 00:16:19,170
Yes.

224
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:25,577
You heard about my grandpa, right?

225
00:16:25,577 --> 00:16:27,050
I did.

226
00:16:27,050 --> 00:16:31,400
Yesterday, I was so shocked when I knew that he had to be admitted to the hospital,

227
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:34,580
so I had to rush to the hospital immediately.

228
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:36,923
Grandpa suddenly got high blood pressure.

229
00:16:36,923 --> 00:16:39,503
Lucky enough, he was sent to the hospital in time.

230
00:16:40,310 --> 00:16:46,315
Do you know that I waited there from the afternoon until 3.00 - 4.00 a.m?

231
00:16:47,060 --> 00:16:48,660
And then?

232
00:16:49,930 --> 00:16:54,250
His voice this time is different from usual.

233
00:16:54,250 --> 00:16:57,204
Am I disturbing you?

234
00:16:58,280 --> 00:17:00,050
I can talk now.

235
00:17:00,050 --> 00:17:02,012
Just go on.

236
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:09,807
I'm just calling to tell you that...

237
00:17:13,398 --> 00:17:15,620
I already quit the job.

238
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:28,307
I hoped to hear him trying to stop me from leaving him.

239
00:17:28,307 --> 00:17:30,850
You heard that already, right?

240
00:17:30,850 --> 00:17:32,973
I'm quitting.

241
00:17:33,730 --> 00:17:35,815
Stop me.

242
00:17:36,330 --> 00:17:38,295
Try to hold me back.

243
00:17:40,930 --> 00:17:43,043
I wish you good luck.

244
00:17:43,490 --> 00:17:49,610
♫ The memory of how much we loved each other ♫

245
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:56,240
But I'm hoping too much.

246
00:17:56,880 --> 00:18:02,940
Our closeness all this time and everything I'm curious of...

247
00:18:05,970 --> 00:18:08,200
were all caused by me alone.

248
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:12,102
It's only I who feels it, and it's all in my head.

249
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:20,077
I wish you good luck, too.

250
00:18:20,618 --> 00:18:23,844
From now, I won't call and bother you often.

251
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:30,226
Silence is also an obvious answer.

252
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:40,930
♫ Because it's hard to forget you ♫

253
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:05,450
♫ I wish I hadn't met you ♫

254
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:11,760
♫ If I could turn back time, I wouldn't look into your eyes ♫

255
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:15,280
♫ And let you give my heart butterflies ♫

256
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:23,980
♫ It'd be better if we didn't know each other... ♫

257
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:32,394
♫ because it's too hard to forget you ♫

258
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:57,387
I'm here to see Miss Dararai.

259
00:19:58,650 --> 00:19:59,890
Did you make an appointment?

260
00:19:59,890 --> 00:20:01,060
I didn't.

261
00:20:01,060 --> 00:20:04,240
Without an appointment, Miss Dararai is not available to see you.

262
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:07,180
She's not ready to meet anyone now.

263
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:09,680
I guess her face still hasn't gotten back to normal.

264
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:12,180
Then, please tell her this.

265
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:14,660
Last night, she said she would sue our agency.

266
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:17,320
We took Donovan to the hospital for a blood test,

267
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:20,940
and a toxin was detected in his body.

268
00:20:20,940 --> 00:20:23,600
If this spreads out,

